    "narrative": "The offensive slate for Ghost Ride the WHIP is anchored by **Mickey Moniak**, whose score of 75.98 makes him today\u2019s primary engine against Tyler Glasnow. **Mickey Moniak** benefits from a massive 14% park boost and a favorable platoon profile, supplemented by Glasnow\u2019s vulnerability to the stolen base (100% SB rating), which aligns perfectly with our need to chase scarce speed. Similarly, **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.72) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (72.09) offer high-ceiling profiles against Davis Martin and Wacha, respectively. While **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** faces a wind-in penalty, the SP skill inflation provided by Wacha keeps his efficiency comfortably in the elite tier. **Austin Riley** (71.42) also projects as a must-start; he is weaponized by a 19% SP skill advantage and, despite the opposing catcher\u2019s elite pop time, his position in the #4 hole provides the necessary RBI volume to buoy our daily totals.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the exclusion of **Alex Freeland**, who fell just short of the cutoff at 58.63. While **Alex Freeland** benefits from the same park and pitcher matchup as **Dalton Rushing**, his projected spot at the bottom of the order (-8% penalty) ultimately relegated him to the bench in favor of more efficient top-of-lineup contributors. Managers should exercise caution regarding the 31% rain risk lingering over our matchups involving **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, and **Giancarlo Stanton**; if these games are delayed or postponed, we lose critical exposure to the high-WHIP, favorable-matchup windows we have identified. Furthermore, while **Corbin Carroll** is started, his score of 62.60 is slightly depressed by a 19% SP skill penalty against Braydon Fisher; however, his elite stolen base potential against a slow-delivering battery makes him non-negotiable for our 5x5 Roto targets.",
